<HelpLayout title="Sensor Setup" category="Sensors & Hardware" description="How to pair your Plantgotchi sensor via Bluetooth, configure WiFi, and understand LED indicators.">
  <p>
    Setting up a Plantgotchi sensor takes about 2 minutes. Here's the full walkthrough.
  </p>

  <h2>Bluetooth Pairing</h2>
  <p>
    All Plantgotchi sensors communicate over Bluetooth Low Energy (BLE). The sensor advertises
    a custom GATT service with UUID <code>0000FE00-0000-1000-8000-00805F9B34FB</code>.
  </p>
  <ol>
    <li>Power on your sensor (insert battery or press the button).</li>
    <li>Open the Plantgotchi app and go to the sensor scan screen.</li>
    <li>The app scans for devices advertising the Plantgotchi service UUID.</li>
    <li>Tap your sensor when it appears in the list.</li>
    <li>The app connects and reads the four data characteristics: moisture, temperature, light, and battery.</li>
  </ol>

  <h2>BLE Data Characteristics</h2>
  <p>
    Each sensor exposes these BLE characteristics (all support Read and Notify):
  </p>
  <table>
    <thead>
      <tr><th>Metric</th><th>UUID suffix</th><th>Format</th><th>Unit</th></tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr><td>Moisture</td><td>FE01</td><td>uint16, little-endian</td><td>0–100%</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Temperature</td><td>FE02</td><td>int16, little-endian</td><td>°C × 100</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Light</td><td>FE03</td><td>uint32, little-endian</td><td>lux</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Battery</td><td>FE04</td><td>uint8</td><td>0–100%</td></tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>
  <p>
    Temperature is sent as an integer multiplied by 100 (e.g., 2350 = 23.50°C) to avoid
    floating-point issues over BLE. The app divides by 100 automatically.
  </p>

  <h2>WiFi Configuration (Solo / PlantCam / Pro)</h2>
  <p>
    Sensors with WiFi capability can connect directly to your network:
  </p>
  <ol>
    <li>After BLE pairing, the app writes WiFi credentials to the Config characteristic (<code>FE05</code>).</li>
    <li>The sensor connects to your WiFi network and begins uploading readings directly to Turso.</li>
    <li>BLE remains active as a fallback if WiFi drops.</li>
  </ol>

  <h2>LED Indicators</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Solid green</strong> — Connected and transmitting normally</li>
    <li><strong>Blinking blue</strong> — BLE advertising, waiting for connection</li>
    <li><strong>Blinking yellow</strong> — Connecting to WiFi</li>
    <li><strong>Red flash</strong> — Battery critically low (below 5%)</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Notification Interval</h2>
  <p>
    By default, sensors send new readings every 30–60 seconds over BLE Notify. You can adjust
    this interval via the Config characteristic to balance between data freshness and battery life.
  </p>
</HelpLayout>
